------------- hamsterdb pro 2.1.9 ------------------------------------

x PRO: review AES usage in read_page; if the page is mmapped then decryption
    is not applied - no, it's ok. encryption disables mmap

o PRO: rebase to vanilla 2.1.9

o PRO: review SIMD code; the problem is that it's never called, because the
    search threshold is always smaller than the minimum block size
    o use fixed block size, otherwise fallback to non-simd search
    o run performance tests

o PRO: refactoring: make AES Encryption stateless and exception safe

o PRO: refactoring: make Compressors stateless and exception safe

o PRO: Can we release an early version of zint32? (undocumented)
    o need to fix erase() handling
    o add full test coverage

o PRO: look for a better compression for DefaultRecordList, i.e.
    o try to move the Zint32 index to a base class
    o Use small index which stores offset + bits for each group
    o Each group is a GroupedVarInt w/ 4 bits per entry; a 64bit
        number can then hold flags for 16 numbers
        o (but maybe increase this to hold at least 32 or 64 numbers, to
            reduce the overhead ratio)
    o a separate bit is used to signal whether the (compressed) number is
        a record id
    o avoid ripple effects by growing/splitting the block
    o Use this index for the default internal record list
    o Use this index for duplicate groups

